data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.DataContractDslDomainModel.Description
data.value: This is the Data Contract Model for the Web Service Software Factory.

data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.DataContractModel.Description
data.value: The root in which all other elements are embedded. Appears as a diagram.

data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.DataContractModel/ImplementationTechnology.Description
data.value: This associates a platform technology with each of the shapes on the design surface. As a result, each shape may acquire additional properties specific for the chosen technology.

data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.DataContractModel/ProjectMappingTable.Description
data.value: The named entries in the ProjectMapping.xml file. A new entry is created each time you create an implementation project structure. The Project Mapping Table entry associates shapes on the design surface with the projects that will contain the code for those shapes.

data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.DataContractModel/Namespace.Description
data.value: This value represents the default XML namespace that will be applied to each shape added to the design surface.

data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.ModelElementReference/Type.Description

data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.DataMember/IsDataMember.Description

data.name: Microsoft.Practices.ServiceFactory.DataContracts.DataMember/CollectionType.Description

data.name: FormatList
data.comment: A list of file format specifiers for the Save dialog box

data.name: DataContractToolToolboxTooltip
data.value: Represents a serializable type that can be reused across multiple services. Its members can be primitive types, enumerated types, other data contracts, and collections.

data.name: DataContractEnumToolToolboxTooltip
data.value: Represents a serializable enumeration that can be reused across multiple services. After adding the Data Contract Enumeration to the design surface, add new values by right-clicking the Values label on the Data Contract Enumeration shape.

data.name: PrimitiveDataTypeCollectionToolToolboxTooltip
data.value: Represents a serializable collection of a primitive type that can be reused across multiple services. To specify what type this is a collection of, use the Item Type property in the Properties window.

data.name: DataContractCollectionToolToolboxTooltip
data.value: Represents a serializable collection that can be reused across multiple services. To specify what type this is a collection of, use the Data Contract property for the collection. To do this, drag a Data Contract shape onto the design surface, drag a Data Contract Collection shape onto the design surface, select the Data Contract Collection, and then click the data contract type in the Data Contract drop-down list in the Properties window.

data.name: FaultContractToolToolboxTooltip
data.value: Represents a serializable SOAP fault that can be reused across multiple services. Its members can be primitive types, enumerated types, other data contracts, and collections.

data.name: AggregationConnectionToolToolboxTooltip
data.value: Creates aggregation relationships between Data Contracts.
